description:
REQUIREMENTS


Practical knowledge in marine or engineering is preferred;
At least 3 years’ relevant experience in a ship owning / ship management company;
Good command of written and spoken English and Mandarin;
Well versed in computer skills;
The candidates who have more experience will be considered as Senior Technical Officer;
Candidates are eligible to work in Hong Kong.

JOB SCOPE 


Reporting to the Ship Managers;
Support the Fleet Managers and Ship Managers in the daily operations of vessels;
Maintain records of vessels’ returns and certification;
Efficient and cost effective supply of stores and spares to vessels;
Communication with vessels’ Class and statutory authorities;
Analysing drydocking quotes and preparing cost comparisons;
Dealing with repair work shops and engine makers.

If you are selected, you will be continuously assessed not only on the basis of your performance, but also on the basis of your behavior. Cultural fit and adherence to Company values is of paramount importance. Attractive remuneration and good benefits will be offered to the chosen candidate. Please apply with a full résumé, salary expectation and contact details to the Human Resources Department by clicking 'Apply Now'. You may also apply by WhatsApp to +852 6117 6848. WhatsApp is for application only, not for follow up communication. Please make sure there is a covering message and specify the position for which you are applying. (Application deadline: 27 Jan 2022)

All applications will be treated in strict confidence and used solely for recruitment purposes.

REQUIREMENTS


University graduate;
Minimum 3 years’ experience in the Shipping Industry is essential as we are willing to train the right candidate;
Customer focused with strong analytical skills;
Reliable team player, who is able to work with energy and creativity across time zones in an international organization;
Good command of written and spoken English is a must; Mandarin skills is preferable; and
Candidates must be eligible to work in Hong Kong.

JOB SCOPE 


To efficiently handle commercial operations for dry bulk ships;
To work closely with other departments in the Company to maximize profits on each voyage;
Maintain close relationships with Owners, Brokers and Service Providers to ensure commercial operations and dispute resolutions are handled efficiently;
Willingness to work remotely from home if required.
If you are selected, you will be continuously assessed not only on the basis of your performance, but also on the basis of your attitude and behavior. Cultural fit and adherence to Company values is of paramount importance. Attractive remuneration and good benefits will be offered to the chosen candidate. Please apply with a full résumé, salary expectation and contact details to the Human Resources Department by clicking 'Apply Now'. You may also apply by WhatsApp to +852 6117 6848. WhatsApp is for application only, not for follow up communication. Please make sure there is a covering message and specify the position for which you are applying. (Application deadline: 22 Jan 2022)


All applications will be treated in strict confidence and used solely for recruitment purposes.
